Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Frontend Software Engineer* with *ModMed*. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack web applications, RAG and AI agents, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the *React.js ecosystem depth and frontend engineering discipline this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an MCP AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — requiring rigorous REST API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across a distributed service surface. I built developer-facing code-generation workflows and API-aware SDK templates to improve the correctness of integrations with platform REST APIs — work that demanded the same precision in interface design that high-quality frontend engineering requires. I also implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith, covering tracing, structured logging, and evaluation hooks, reducing end-to-end latency by 60% and LLM API costs by 50% through targeted concurrency and routing optimizations. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed directly to user-facing frontend development. I developed an Identity & Access Management platform built with *React*, Spring Boot, and AWS — supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications — where I owned user-facing features and built reusable component architecture that scaled across the entire product. I also designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via expiring signed URLs, and built an internal support chatbot using LangChain and RAG with a PostgreSQL vector store that reduced ticket resolution time by 20%. Together, these roles have prepared me to *own and deliver user-facing features, reusable front-end components, and scalable React-based systems that directly serve healthcare providers and patients*.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development, GPU-accelerated computing, and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *the cross-functional, user-empathetic engineering culture and agile collaboration that ModMed values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion to generate industry-standard fashion designs, leveraging CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster for model training and fine-tuning. I was responsible for managing the full model development lifecycle — from data preparation and training runs to inference optimization using vLLM and deployment via Hugging Face — ensuring both performance and secure, efficient model serving. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring *the clear technical communication and cross-team collaboration this role values*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to ModMed's team and its mission to transform how specialty practices deliver patient care.

I have always been passionate about *placing doctors and patients at the center of care and innovating boldly in healthcare technology* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *modernizing medicine through intelligent, specialty-specific cloud software*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

